FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE - ZAMBIA: (NORTH-WESTERN) BOVINE, NOT TYPED, OIE
***********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Sat 13 Jan 2018
Source: OIE WAHID [edited] http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=25698


Foot and mouth disease, Zambia
----------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 13 Jan 2018 Dr Yona Sinkala, Director, Department of Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture and Livestock, Lusaka, Zambia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification (final report)
Date of start of the event: 27 Jun 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 12 Jul 2017
Report date: 13 Jan 2018
Date submitted to OIE: 13 Jan 2018
Date event resolved: 31 Dec 2017
Reason for notification: First occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: Not typed
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic and advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (3)
Outbreak 1: Chinyamalitapi Vet Camp, Zambezi, North-Western
Date of start of the outbreak: 27 Jun 2017
Outbreak status: resolved 31 Dec 2017
Epidemiological unit: other
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 30 000 / 7500 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak 2: Chavuma, Chavuma, North-Western
Date of start of the outbreak: 27 Jul 2017
Outbreak status: resolved 31 Dec 2017
Epidemiological unit: other
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 7633 / 3355 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak 3: Watopa and Mumbezhi Vet Camps, Kabombo, North-Western
Date of start of the outbreak: 2 Aug 2017
Outbreak status: resolved 31 Dec 2017
Epidemiological unit: other
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 6954 / 700 / 0 / 0 / 0

Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 44 587 / 11 555 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]:
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 25.92 / 0.00 / 0.00 / 0.00
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: illegal movement of animals; contact with infected animal(s) at grazing/watering; fomites (humans, vehicles, feed, etc.)

Epidemiological comments: The affected areas have cattle under a traditional free-range management system, with all ages of animals showing clinical signs

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; quarantine; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; traceability; no treatment of affected animals;

Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)
Administrative division / Species / Total vaccinated / Details
North-Western / Cattle / 18 215 / -

Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Central Veterinary Laboratory Research Institute (National laboratory) / Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 12 Jul 2017 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

